view map send flowers resources more obituaries for rawson haverty looking for an obituary for a different person with this name rawson haverty sr obituary condolences familyplaced death notice rawson haverty sr rawson haverty sr died peacefully on friday january   surrounded by his family he was lovingly cared for by the sisters doctors and nurses at st josephs hospital where he had served as chairman of the hospital board of directors for many years rawson haverty was born in atlanta november   son of clarence haverty and elizabeth rawson haverty he graduated from e rivers elementary school north fulton high school and the university of georgia in the class of  he was a member of the sae fraternity and served as its treasurer and house manager he joined haverty furniture companies inc in august  the company founded by his grandfather james joseph haverty in  he worked in the credit department until  when he was called into active duty service as a nd lieutenant in the u s army he commanded tank companies in the third and eleventh armored divisions he participated in the invasion of normandy dday plus  the battle of normandy the battle of france the battle of belgium and the battle of germany his unit met the russians on the elbe river he received among other decorations the bronze star a commendation ribbon the belgium croix de guerre with palm the order of leopold with palm cavalier class  belgium and the european theatre ribbon with four campaign stars he was honorably discharged in  with the rank of major he rejoined haverty furniture companies inc in january  he held the offices of secretary vice president and treasurer and served as president from  to  as chief executive officer from  to  as chief executive officer from  to  and as chairman from  through  at end of  he retired from active duty and was named chairman emeritus he was a director of the company for  years from  until  he served as chairman of the board of bank south corporation of atlanta from  to  he is a former director of southwestern life corporation dallas texas  colonial stores inc of atlanta  j m tull industries inc atlanta  barclays american corporation charlotte nc  and piedmont airlines inc winstonsalem nc  he was a member of the faculty of merchants in the national retail furniture associations school for executives northwestern university of chicago and with the southern retail furniture association university of north carolina at chapel hill he served a three year term as distinguished practitionerlecturer for the college of business administration at the university of georgia he has served as director of the national retail merchants association from  until  and as director of the executive committee of the american retail association from  to  he was named all american merchant of the furniture industry and was elected to the american furniture hall of fame in october  he is a former chairman of marta  member of the fulton county industrial authority  director and past president of the atlanta chamber of commerce  honorary life member of the atlanta junior chamber of commerce  president of forward atlanta  member of atlanta progress inc president and director of kiwanis club of atlanta director of the commerce club of atlanta  former director of the atlanta better business club chairman of the organizational committee to form the georgia retail merchants association  he served as chairman of the board of trustees of st josephs hospital of atlanta from  to  he served on the board of advisors of st josephs home for boys washington ga from  to  and elected its first president and first honorary life trustee he was chairman of the archdiocese finance committee of the catholic archdiocese of atlanta from  to  he served as trustee of the westminster schools of atlanta  president of the university of georgia alumni association  chairman of the university of georgia loyalty fund drive  recipient of the university of georgia alumni merit award  and trustee of the university of georgia foundation he is past president of the atlanta school of art and honorary life member of the high museum of art he is past president of the hub of the south chapter of the association of the united states army he is an honorary trustee of high point university high point nc he is the author of three books aint the roses sweet my wifes family and a history of haverty furniture company theres no place like home he is a member of the roman catholic church holy spirit parish in atlanta he was named man of the year by the catholic archodiocese of atlanta in  and was in  made a knight commander of the order of st gregory the great by pope john paul ii he is preceded in death by his grandson j jeffrey langford he is survived by his sister betty haverty smith of atlanta and his beloved wife of  years the former margaret middleton munnerlyn of jacksonville florida his three daughters peggy haverty glover of ponte verda florida jane middleton haverty of atlanta and liz haverty bousson of easthampton new york and his two sons rawson haverty jr and ben m haverty both of atlanta and his  grandchildren there will be a visitation on monday january th from  to  at h m patterson  son springhill  spring street nw atlanta ga  a funeral service will be on tuesday january th at  am at holy spirit catholic church  northside drive nw atlanta ga  private interment will be at westview cemetery online memorials may be posted at wwwmemcom in lieu of flowers donations may be made in mr havertys memory to the mary e haverty foundation co mrs kim wade bank of america  peachtree street suite  atlanta ga  or to the st josephs mercy foundation  peachtree dunwoody rd ne atlanta ga  h m patterson  son spring hill published in the atlanta journalconstitution from jan  to jan   read more remember share memories or express condolences below  entries the guest book is expired please restore the guest book to share in the life story for rawson haverty sr to the haverty family i remember mr haverty because my father james wright worked for the family forpersita wrightbraswell restore the guest book resources send funeral flowers donate to charity find advice  support funeral etiquette how to write a sympathy note  back to todays obituaries planning guide free funeral planning guide compliments of hm patterson  sonspring hill chapel download now notify friends and family add the email addresses of friends or family members youd like to notify about this obituary to invalid to email from invalid from email message optional please provide me with special offers and discounts from legacycom and selected partners emails will be sent directly from legacycom we respect your privacy and will not sell your information to a third party you may opt out at any time see privacy policy for details your email was sent successfully return to the obituary send another email share there was an error sending your email please try again we apologize for the inconvenience havertys  wikipedia havertys from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search haverty furniture companies inc type public traded as nyse hvt sp  component industry furniture founded  headquarters atlanta georgia usa number of locations  key people clarence h smith chairman president and ceo richard b hare executive vp and cfo steven g burdette executive vp and coo j edward clary executive vp and cio richard d gallagher executive vp merchandising revenue us million  net income us million  number of employees   website wwwhavertyscom haverty furniture companies inc havertys is a retail furniture company founded in  beginning with a single store in downtown atlanta havertys has grown to become one of the top furniture retailers in the south and central united states contents  history  key dates  community service  environmental impact  references  external links historyedit havertys was founded by james joseph jj haverty and his brother michael in  the first store was located at  east hunter street now  martin luther king jr drive in atlanta georgia by the third year the new company moved to a larger location in  jj and michael entered a partnership with the owner of a neighboring furniture store amos g rhodes forming the rhodeshaverty furniture company a year and a half after the first rhodeshaverty store opened jj haverty moved westward to st louis missouri with his family to expand and soon after bought interest in a number of smaller showrooms it wasnt until  that jj returned his family back to atlanta and went on the road to open more stores by   stores were open and thriving jj havertys son clarence who first began in the business by sweeping floors rose to a leadership position and wished for a larger role in the business the partnership with rhodes was dissolved amicably and with the flip of a coin  of the stores were divided between rhodes and haverty the main atlanta location was purchased outright by jj haverty and the business took back its original name of haverty furniture company following the split with rhodes the company expanded across the south the atlanta headquarters outgrew their facility and moved to a larger sixstory building in  also during this period jj haverty and amos rhodes formed another partnership this time to erect the rhodeshaverty building which would remain atlantas tallest structure until  in the late s the company took advantage of the booming stock market and went public the stock sale took place on october   four weeks later the market crashed havertys strong financial positions enabled the company to weather the difficult years ahead clarence haverty who had run the business for many years was officially named president in  at which time his father jj became chairman of the board in october  just short of his st birthday founder jj haverty died in december  the united states entered world war ii and the company faced hard times brought on by the rationing of furniture production materials when the war ended pentup demand for consumer goods caused sales to surge the company seized the opportunity to remodel older stores and open new locations clarence havertys son rawson returned from war and assumed the position of corporate secretary the company continued to prosper during the s by  there were  stores across ten states clarence haverty decided to step down as president and rawson took on the role by  the year of the companys th anniversary havertys added four more locations that year also saw the passing of clarence haverty at the age of  by the end of the s retail trends were changing and downtown stores were replaced by stores closer to the growing suburban populations rawson haverty led the company through this transition as president and chief executive officer until  when he was elected as chairman of the board another one of the founder’s grandsons frank mcgaughey jr who had been with the company since  accepted the title of president in the late s havertys embarked upon a comprehensive revitalization program upgrading most of the companys stores enhanced lighting and display areas were the primary improvements with some stores also expanding in size the revitalization included closing the last downtown atlanta store havertys remained the areas largest furniture retailer with locations distributed throughout the metropolitan area frank mcgaughey jr added ceo to his title in addition to president in  he held this post until his retirement in  when john e slater was named president and ceo slater joined the company in  and had spent his entire career with havertys in august  the companys stock listing moved from the nasdaq exchange to the new york stock exchange as havertys witnessed the turn of another century the company underwent many changes an initiative began to develop havertys own brand of furniture starting with just a few items in february  most of the companys sales volume is now of merchandise exclusively designed sourced and produced under the havertys brand progress continued and  stores were in business by the beginning of  when the furniture retailer saw another change in leadership rawson haverty retired from the board and took the title chairman emeritus grandson of jj haverty clarence clancy h ridley elected to the board of directors in  took rawsons place as chairman of the board clancy provided continuity and guidance when jjs great grandson clarence h smith who spent his entire career experiencing all facets of the company became president and ceo in  rawson haverty continued to attend board meetings until his death in  at the age of  frank magaughey jr also died soon after in  at the age of  growth of the internet presented havertys with another opportunity and in  the company revamped the website by march  customers could browse through products and make purchases online in  havertys built their southeastern distribution center in braselton georgia since then it has grown to more than  sq ft the year  marked yet another change for company leadership as l phillip humann succeeded clancy ridley as chairman of the board clancy was elected chairman emeritus in  president and ceo clarence h smith who had been a member of the board of directors since  succeeded l phillip humann as chairman of the board mr humann remains a member of the board as lead director havertys has expanded to three distribution centers to support over  showrooms in  states additional information is available on the companys website havertyscom key datesedit  first store opened by jj haverty and his brother michael  partnership with amos g rhodes to form rhodeshaverty furniture  jj haverty and son clarence split with rhodes and reestablish haverty furniture co  company went public as haverty furniture companies inc  clarence haverty becomes president  clarence havertys son rawson appointed president  jj havertys grandson frank mcgaughey jr named president  jay e slater becomes president  stock moves to new york stock exchange  th store opened  launch of own brand of furniture  clarence h smith jj’s great grandson named president  first online sale community serviceedit over the years havertys has contributed time labor money and furnishings to national causes such as united way american red cross the american cancer foundation the american heart association and many moreneutrality is disputed in  the company became a national sponsor of the american cancer society making strides against breast cancer walk furnishings and accessories were donated to families featured on extreme makeover home edition in several instances local employees volunteered their time to help in the process in the atlanta area havertys has made an impact on the high museum of art marta saint josephs hospital and many charities associated with the catholic archdiocese of atlanta environmental impactedit havertys has invested  in equipment that recycles approximately  tons of corrugated material and  tons of styrofoam each year a line of ecofriendly furniture with innovative elements designed to leave a smaller environmental footprint was introduced in  referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n haverty rawson  aint the roses sweet haverty furniture companies inc haverty rawson  there’s no place like home haverty furniture companies inc smith william rawson  villa clare the purposeful life and timeless art collection of jj haverty mercer university press answerscom haverty furniture companies inc profile retrieved december    furniture today top  us furniture retailers retrieved december    the city of atlanta rhodeshaverty building retrieved december    new york stock exchange haverty furniture companies inc profile retrieved december    home furnishings business keeping between the lines retrieved december    home furnishings business havertys sales up retrieved december    furniture today phil humann officially becomes havertys chairman retrieved december    haverty furniture companies inchavertys today ret