 four more locations that year also saw the passing of clarence haverty at the age of  by the end of the s retail trends were changing and downtown stores were replaced by stores closer to the growing suburban populations rawson haverty led the company through this transition as president and chief executive officer until  when he was elected as chairman of the board another one of the founder’s grandsons frank mcgaughey jr who had been with the company since  accepted the title of president in the late s havertys embarked upon a comprehensive revitalization program upgrading most of the companys stores enhanced lighting and display areas were the primary improvements with some stores also expanding in size the revitalization included closing the last downtown atlanta store havertys remained the areas largest furniture retailer with locations distributed throughout the metropolitan area frank mcgaughey jr added ceo to his title in addition to president in  he held this post until his retirement in  when john e slater was named president and ceo slater joined the company in  and had spent his entire career with havertys in august  the companys stock listing moved from the nasdaq exchange to the new york stock exchange as havertys witnessed the turn of another century the company underwent many changes an initiative began to develop havertys own brand of furniture starting with just a few items in february  most of the companys sales volume is now of merchandise exclusively designed sourced and produced under the havertys brand progress continued and  stores were in business by the beginning of  when the furniture retailer saw another change in leadership rawson haverty retired from the board and took the title chairman emeritus grandson of jj haverty clarence clancy h ridley elected to the board of directors in  took rawsons place as chairman of the board clancy provided continuity and guidance when jjs great grandson clarence h smith who spent his entire career experiencing all facets of the company became president and ceo in  rawson haverty continued to attend board meetings until his death in  at the age of  frank magaughey jr also died soon after in  at the age of  growth of the internet presented havertys with another opportunity and in  the company revamped the website by march  customers could browse through products and make purchases online in  havertys built their southeastern distribution center in braselton georgia since then it has grown to more than  sq ft the year  marked yet another change for company leadership as l phillip humann succeeded clancy ridley as chairman of the board clancy was elected chairman emeritus in  president and ceo clarence h smith who had been a member of the board of directors since  succeeded l phillip humann as chairman of the board mr humann remains a member of the board as lead director havertys has expanded to three distribution centers to support over  showrooms in  states additional information is available on the companys website havertyscom key datesedit  first store opened by jj haverty and his brother michael  partnership with amos g rhodes to form rhodeshaverty furniture  jj haverty and son clarence split with rhodes and reestablish haverty furniture co  company went public as haverty furniture companies inc  clarence haverty becomes president  clarence havertys son rawson appointed president  jj havertys grandson frank mcgaughey jr named president  jay e slater becomes president  stock moves to new york stock exchange  th store opened  launch of own brand of furniture  clarence h smith jj’s great grandson named president  first online sale community serviceedit over the years havertys has contributed time labor money and furnishings to national causes such as united way american red cross the american cancer foundation the american heart association and many moreneutrality is disputed in  the company became a national sponsor of the american cancer society making strides against breast cancer walk furnishings and accessories were donated to families featured on extreme makeover home edition in several instances local employees volunteered their time to help in the process in the atlanta area havertys has made an impact on the high museum of art marta saint josephs hospital and many charities associated with the catholic archdiocese of atlanta environmental impactedit havertys has invested  in equipment that recycles approximately  tons of corrugated material and  tons of styrofoam each year a line of ecofriendly furniture with innovative elements designed to leave a smaller environmental footprint was introduced in  referencesedit  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n haverty rawson  aint the roses sweet haverty furniture companies inc haverty rawson  there’s no place like home haverty furniture companies inc smith william rawson  villa clare the purposeful life and timeless art collection of jj haverty mercer university press answerscom haverty furniture companies inc profile retrieved december    furniture today top  us furniture retailers retrieved december    the city of atlanta rhodeshaverty building retrieved december    new york stock exchange haverty furniture companies inc profile retrieved december    home furnishings business keeping between the lines retrieved december    home furnishings business havertys sales up retrieved december    furniture today phil humann officially becomes havertys chairman retrieved december    haverty furniture companies inchavertys today retrieved december    a b haverty furniture companies inc community service retrieved december    business wire havertys commits of american cancer society retrieved december    cnbc havertys furnishes entire home for extreme makeover home edition retrieved december    haverty furniture companies inc ecofriendly retrieved december   external linksedit havertys official website tour  years of havertys history havertys at facebook havertys locations retrieved from httpse